<m1><ue5><m0>In new blow to Samper,<ql>
finance minister resigns<ql>
<m1><ue5><ep>
<m0>   <m0>BOGOTA<m0> (--) In the latest blow to his scandal-plagued administration, President Ernesto Samper accepted the resignation of his finance minister Monday.<ep>
   Guillermo Perry submitted his resignation over the weekend, saying his departure would enable him to better defend the president against charges he took money from the Cali drug cartel to finance his 1994 campaign.<ep>
   Samper named former Agriculture Minister Jose Antonio Ocampo, head of the government's economic planning office, to replace Perry.<ql>
